{"url": "https://www.harpersbazaar.com/celebrity/latest/a20719958/not-all-spice-girls-invited-royal-wedding/", "text": "2 min read\n\nStop right now! In case you missed it, the Spice Girls had a surprise reunion in London on Saturday, in honor of Victoria Beckham (a.k.a. Posh Spice) on her 50th birthday.\n\nAlong with Beckham, the four other members of the group were present, including Mel B (Scary Spice), Melanie C (Sporty Spice), Emma Bunton (Baby Spice), and Geri Halliwell (Ginger Spice).\n\nThe moment was documented on Beckham\u2019s Instagram account, where the designer included a pic with her former bandmates and wrote, \u201cThe best gift to be reunited!! Thank you to all my friends and family for celebrating with me. Kisses! xxx.\u201d\n\nOn husband David\u2019s Instagram, we also got a glimpse of the group\u2019s impromptu performance of their hit 1998 single \u201cStop.\u201d In a video shared by the retired pro footballer, the group sings along to the track in front of A-list attendees including Tom Cruise, Eva Longoria, and Gordon Ramsay.\n\nFor the celebratory evening, Beckham chose a dress from her own line\u2019s Spring/Summer \u201924 collection\u2014a sheer seafoam gown that featured asymmetrical arm holes and gathered fabric around the sides, as well as ruched seams that looked like flowers. Underneath the dress, Beckham wore a black bra-and-panties set, and she accessorized with a thick silver cuff.\n\nHeading into the ceremony, the birthday girl was seen coming in on crutches (she broke her foot while working out in February), and on her way out, her hubby actually carried her on his back. The fashion designer enjoyed the support of not only her friends, but also her family, as all four of her kids\u2014 Brooklyn, 25, Romeo, 21, Cruz, 19, and Harper, 12\u2014were present.\n\nThe fashion designer gushed in a different Instagram post later, writing, \u201cI don\u2019t think I\u2019ve ever felt as loved as I did last night. Thank you all for coming 